WEBVTT

00:00.954 --> 00:02.834
Previously on The O.C.:

00:03.154 --> 00:04.834
How many wines have we tasted?

00:04.834 --> 00:05.874
I stopped taking notes.

00:05.874 --> 00:07.314
A little too much Indian spirit, huh?

00:07.314 --> 00:09.074
Well, drive back in the morning.

00:09.074 --> 00:10.194
I need to go home.

00:10.194 --> 00:11.914
The Nana's not nice.
I love her, but she's not.

00:11.914 --> 00:12.754
It's kind of part of her charm.

00:12.754 --> 00:14.914
I hate this state!
I hate the sunshine!

00:14.914 --> 00:18.034
I hate the ocean!
I hate Schwarzenegger!

00:21.754 --> 00:22.794
I don't believe it, Ryan.

00:22.794 --> 00:24.754
Bright Eyes has two albums in the top ten.

00:24.754 --> 00:25.674
Are you okay with that?

00:25.674 --> 00:28.714
Yeah, I just feel like the rest of the world has finally caught up to me.

00:28.714 --> 00:31.594
- It's a little bit scary.
- Yeah, it's a lot scary.

00:31.594 --> 00:33.194
Tell me I'm still special.

00:37.394 --> 00:38.354
Sethela.

00:38.354 --> 00:40.354
Nanala.
How you feeling?

00:40.354 --> 00:43.194
Oh, if you were all that interested, you would have called me.

00:43.194 --> 00:46.114
And would it kill you to cash that birthday check I sent you?

00:46.114 --> 00:49.554
- I'm finished sending you things.
- Okay, I'm sorry, I forgot.

00:49.554 --> 00:50.954
You make my life very difficult.

00:50.954 --> 00:54.434
No, I'm sure that $20 outstanding has the bank just going crazy.

00:54.434 --> 00:56.314
Yeah, smart ass.
Where's your father?

00:56.314 --> 00:57.594
- I don't know...
- Who is it, Seth?

00:57.594 --> 01:00.514
Actually, my mom just came in if you want to talk to her.

01:00.514 --> 01:02.114
- It's The Nana.
- No.

01:02.114 --> 01:03.394
What do you want me..?

01:03.394 --> 01:05.674
Hello, my dad just showed up.

01:05.674 --> 01:08.114
Awkward family moment avoided for everyone but me.

01:08.114 --> 01:09.994
- Love you.
- Yeah? You coulïve fooled me.

01:09.994 --> 01:11.234
It's The Nana.

01:11.594 --> 01:15.234
Oh. Ma!
Hey! How are you?

01:15.714 --> 01:17.674
Why does he always get so much louder when he talks to her?

01:17.674 --> 01:18.914
They're a family of screamers.

01:18.914 --> 01:20.994
- How's your grandma feeling?
- The Nana. Ryan, please.

01:20.994 --> 01:24.154
"Grandma" invokes homemade cookies and maybe someonewho's actually nice to you.

01:24.154 --> 01:26.514
The Nana, definitely not nice to you, or me.

01:26.514 --> 01:28.394
- But she's doing great.
- Full remission.

01:28.394 --> 01:31.874
Which confirms my suspicion that she is, in fact, immortal.

01:31.874 --> 01:33.554
What? So soon?

01:33.554 --> 01:34.954
Oh, my God, Ma.

01:35.914 --> 01:37.554
Let me call you back.

01:38.034 --> 01:40.434
- What happened?
- Is everything all right?

01:41.714 --> 01:44.714
The Nana...headed for the altar.

01:44.714 --> 01:46.234
She's getting married?

01:46.234 --> 01:48.114
Pack your bags.
We're going to Miami.

01:48.354 --> 01:49.154
All right.

01:49.274 --> 01:51.274
Shuffleboard, mahjongg, dinner at 4:00.

01:51.634 --> 01:53.194
This is gonna be the best spring break ever.

