contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:24.261 --> 02:25.141
Hey, mon.

02:25.141 --> 02:27.701
Now, I know you think you're excited about Miami,

02:27.701 --> 02:30.981
but I cannot wait for you to meet the guys at Nana's condo.

02:30.981 --> 02:34.381
We got Abe, we got Stu, we got Stanley.

02:34.381 --> 02:36.341
Although I think Stanley may have passed on.

02:36.341 --> 02:38.981
- He had a prostate thing. I hope not...
- I can't go.

02:38.981 --> 02:40.501
What? Why not?

02:40.501 --> 02:41.861
'Cause, you know, everything with me and Marissa.

02:41.861 --> 02:42.821
Is awesome.

02:42.821 --> 02:44.501
Fine, okay, but, you know, there's Trey.

02:44.501 --> 02:46.021
Who's also doing awesome.

02:46.021 --> 02:48.581
Ryan, face it, you've got no excuses.

02:48.581 --> 02:50.741
Everything's great.
You deserve a vacation.

02:50.741 --> 02:52.941
We, actually, deserve a vacation, Ryan.

02:52.941 --> 02:54.421
And it would mean a lot to my dad.

02:54.741 --> 02:56.421
Yeah, yeah, he is kind of worked up.

02:56.421 --> 02:58.381
- He's gonna need some company.
- Well, he's got you.

02:58.381 --> 03:00.381
I can't, man.
My schedule's all booked up.

03:00.381 --> 03:04.261
I got pinochle with the ladies on Saturday, bridge Sunday with the fellas.

03:04.261 --> 03:06.381
I still got to call and see if I can get on that bingo cruise.

03:06.381 --> 03:08.541
That's gonna be freaking awesome.
What about you and Summer?

03:08.541 --> 03:12.221
I'm going to go over there, I'm going to apologize extremely sincerely,

03:12.221 --> 03:15.421
and then I'm gonna get out of town before I can do anything else wrong.

03:15.421 --> 03:19.301
- What do you say?
- Miami. Miami.

03:28.061 --> 03:28.981
Honey?

03:29.301 --> 03:30.661
Do you have my American Advantage number?

03:30.661 --> 03:33.661
I'm on AA.com and I'm trying to use my miles to upgrade.

03:33.661 --> 03:35.821
You know me, I hate sitting in the middle.

03:35.821 --> 03:38.181
It's in my purse.
But what's the rush, sweetie?

03:38.181 --> 03:40.141
It's not like she's getting married tomorrow.

03:40.141 --> 03:43.101
I know, it's just...
I love my mother.

03:43.301 --> 03:45.381
- But who else would?
- That's terrible.

03:45.381 --> 03:47.301
You wouldn't say the same thing about your dad?

03:47.301 --> 03:48.301
You make a good point.

03:48.301 --> 03:50.061
You know, she was just so happy on the phone.

03:50.061 --> 03:52.301
I just want to make sure everything works out for her.

03:52.301 --> 03:55.701
Great. Especially after the year she's had.

03:56.261 --> 03:59.661
- You are a good son.
- Oh, yeah?

03:59.661 --> 04:03.781
- How about husband?
- Definitely top five.

04:05.421 --> 04:08.101
Miami, huh?
Well, have a hell of a time, man.

04:08.101 --> 04:10.261
- Thanks, you'll be all right?
- Don't worry, Mom.

04:10.261 --> 04:11.741
I'll be fine.

04:14.621 --> 04:16.461
Uh, yo, Ry, look, I got to jump.

04:16.461 --> 04:19.541
Probably the landlord complaining about something.

04:21.581 --> 04:23.861
Have fun.
See ya.

04:28.661 --> 04:30.181
Definitely not the landlord.

04:30.501 --> 04:31.901
Hey, you.

04:33.541 --> 04:34.541
So...

04:36.221 --> 04:40.141
I just wanted to come by to say thanks again for not selling me out.

04:41.061 --> 04:42.301
Have you met Don Julio?

04:42.821 --> 04:46.461
Yeah, me and Don go way back.

04:46.461 --> 04:49.021
- Thanks for the gift.
- Oh, that's not the gift.

04:49.461 --> 04:55.501
I figure, a guy's been in prison for 18 months, probably got pretty lonely.

05:00.421 --> 05:02.301
You have no idea.

05:10.581 --> 05:12.261
Hey, Summer.
Busy?

05:12.781 --> 05:14.941
- What do you want, Cohen?
- To...talk.

05:18.141 --> 05:21.181
- Hold my bag.
- Anything for my Million Dollar Baby.

05:22.101 --> 05:23.301
Um...so look...

05:23.301 --> 05:25.301
- I just came to apologize.
- Why?

05:25.301 --> 05:28.301
'Cause I was humiliated in front of all your oh- so- hip,

05:28.301 --> 05:31.061
super- dorked- out, indie- music- loving, comic- book geeks

05:31.061 --> 05:34.621
who looked at me like I was some dimwit Orange County ho?

05:36.061 --> 05:37.861
But that was never my intention. Okay?

05:37.861 --> 05:40.981
I really only wanted you there to be a part of everything with me.

05:40.981 --> 05:44.541
Look, there's no point in your apologizing because you can no longer make me upset.

05:44.541 --> 05:46.381
You're just immune to my charms?

05:46.381 --> 05:47.621
Working on it.

05:47.701 --> 05:49.381
But you know what I could use?

05:49.701 --> 05:51.221
A time- out.

05:54.701 --> 05:58.301
Well, you know, good.
That, actually, 'cause...

05:58.301 --> 06:02.101
that's good timing, 'cause I'm headed to Miami to see The Nana, so...

06:02.101 --> 06:03.501
Well, perfect.

06:03.501 --> 06:06.541
Yeah, go to Miami, get wasted and wind up on Music Video

06:06.541 --> 06:08.781
- Nation's Spring Break Special.
- It's actually nothing like that.

06:08.781 --> 06:10.581
The only thing I'm going to be drinking is Metamucil.

06:10.581 --> 06:12.701
Oh, yeah. Like I'm going to believe that.

06:12.701 --> 06:14.981
Just go.
Go sow your oats.

06:14.981 --> 06:18.541
Get all of your Coheny, Cohenish Cohenisms out of your system.

06:18.541 --> 06:19.821
And when I get back?

06:20.741 --> 06:22.261
We'll see.

06:35.181 --> 06:40.901
So just imagine, a whole weekend of nothing but this.

06:41.861 --> 06:44.261
If you could just hold that thought till, like, next weekend.

06:44.261 --> 06:49.061
- Why, are you going somewhere?
- Uh...yeah, actually, Miami.

06:50.781 --> 06:52.861
South Beach for a little spring break action?

06:52.861 --> 06:53.981
Meet some college girls?

06:53.981 --> 06:56.421
Not quite. I'm going with Seth and Sandy to see The Nana.

06:56.421 --> 06:59.301
Oh, that's really sweet.
That'll be fun.

06:59.301 --> 07:01.141
Yeah, no, it will be.
It's just, I don't know.

07:01.141 --> 07:03.501
I feel kind of weird leaving Trey here by himself.

07:03.821 --> 07:06.301
- I can hang out with him.
- Yeah, really?

07:06.301 --> 07:08.941
Because I was kind of gonna help him find a job.

07:09.941 --> 07:12.141
- I got it covered.
- Thanks, I owe you.

07:12.581 --> 07:15.581
Mm, yes. You do.
You do owe me.

07:15.581 --> 07:19.381
A whole weekend of nothing but this.

07:24.781 --> 07:25.901
That, I can do.

07:26.781 --> 07:28.061
All right, now, you've got all the numbers?

07:28.061 --> 07:30.221
My cell phone? The Fontainebleau? The Nana?

07:30.221 --> 07:31.621
I got the numbers.

07:32.541 --> 07:35.021
You remember how to set the alarm to no delay?

07:35.021 --> 07:36.821
And if the alarm goes off, the code word is..?

07:36.821 --> 07:38.621
"Greased Lightning."
I got it.

07:38.621 --> 07:39.941
Yes. Do you need any cash?

07:39.941 --> 07:41.821
- I have plenty of money.
- I gassed up your car.

07:41.821 --> 07:43.901
- Which I so appreciate.
- Are you going to be fine?

07:43.901 --> 07:47.101
- I'll be fine.
- I love you.

07:48.141 --> 07:50.541
The question is, are you going to be okay?

07:54.381 --> 07:56.141
Fellas, you got everything?

07:56.141 --> 07:58.861
I got my cardigan, my orthopedic shoes and my humidifier.

07:58.861 --> 08:01.141
Now take me to my people.

08:35.581 --> 08:37.501
Is Carter in the office?

08:48.781 --> 08:50.581
In the immortal words of Will Smith--

08:50.861 --> 08:53.541
- Thank you--
- "Welcome to Miami."

08:53.541 --> 08:56.541
There's too many young, tan, healthy people here. I don't like it.

08:56.541 --> 08:58.861
Let's check in anyway.
Hey, who wants some dinner?

08:58.861 --> 09:01.381
Yeah, it is 4:00 p. m. in Orange County.

09:01.381 --> 09:03.261
They put us on the early bird circuit.

09:07.941 --> 09:09.701
I have the weekend to myself.

09:10.181 --> 09:12.861
I thought we could roll up our sleeves, really dig in,

09:12.861 --> 09:14.941
and maybe even get a few issues ahead.

09:14.941 --> 09:17.541
Well, I'd hold onto that thought if I were you.

09:17.861 --> 09:19.221
Turns out, Newport Living,

09:19.221 --> 09:22.301
which I thought would be the last nail in the coffin that is my career,

09:22.301 --> 09:25.101
is actually the thing that saved it.

09:27.061 --> 09:29.461
You got another job offer?

09:29.781 --> 09:33.301
- Well, Carter, that's great.
- Thanks.

09:35.221 --> 09:37.461
Yeah, so I fly out on Monday.

09:37.701 --> 09:40.141
- Fly out where?
- New York.

09:40.141 --> 09:42.981
That's where the job is and they're relocating me.

09:43.301 --> 09:44.821
You're leaving?

09:45.141 --> 09:46.301
I am.

09:47.461 --> 09:50.861
But my publisher is lining up someone to replace me.

09:50.861 --> 09:54.501
You know, someone who is smarter, and better at this than I am.

09:54.501 --> 09:55.941
So...

09:57.581 --> 10:01.301
I hope you don't think I'm jumping ship.

10:01.301 --> 10:02.701
Because you are.

10:05.541 --> 10:08.181
It's really great.

10:18.941 --> 10:21.861
I was thinking we could have a farewell dinner.

10:22.661 --> 10:23.941
You know what?
We should.

10:23.941 --> 10:26.181
Great. I'll make a reservation at Arches.

10:26.181 --> 10:29.381
Or you could come by the house tomorrow.

10:29.381 --> 10:30.461
I'll cook.

10:36.301 --> 10:37.941
Man! I thought Newport was nice.

10:37.941 --> 10:38.821
This is something, huh?

10:38.821 --> 10:41.581
Yeah, if you're a fan of that vibrant night life.

10:41.581 --> 10:43.381
Hey, why can't we go see The Nana tonight?

10:43.381 --> 10:45.021
You know The Nana and her schedule.

10:45.021 --> 10:46.381
Friday night's mahjongg.

10:46.381 --> 10:47.461
- What?
- Yeah.

10:47.461 --> 10:48.701
Since when is Friday night mahjongg?

10:48.701 --> 10:50.461
It totally throws off my schedule.

10:50.461 --> 10:51.741
Breathe it in, boys.

10:51.741 --> 10:54.661
We've got a weekend away with nothing to worry about.

11:03.821 --> 11:06.181
- Sorry.
- Marissa. What's up?

11:06.181 --> 11:07.981
Ryan took off for Miami, huh?

11:07.981 --> 11:12.261
Yeah, so I just wanted you to know that while he's gone, I'm here.

11:13.181 --> 11:14.101
Cool.

11:14.461 --> 11:17.621
Uh...you know, you don't have to, if you don't want to.

11:17.621 --> 11:19.101
No, I want to.

11:19.101 --> 11:22.261
And you know, I thought maybe tomorrow we could go job hunting.

11:22.261 --> 11:24.221
That sounds great.

11:25.021 --> 11:27.421
I thought with Ryan gone, I was going to be all alone in Newport.

11:27.421 --> 11:29.021
No, not on my watch.

11:29.341 --> 11:31.581
- So I'll see you tomorrow?
- Can't wait.

11:49.101 --> 11:52.301
You and Marissa Cooper?
Yeah, right.

11:55.541 --> 11:57.861
- It's not like that.
- Sure isn't.

11:57.861 --> 12:01.701
Not in this lifetime, or in this town.

12:21.037 --> 12:23.117
- Adios...
- Your move!

12:23.117 --> 12:26.037
- Huh? You're playing with him?
- Yeah, I'm playing with him.

12:26.037 --> 12:27.837
- I thought you were playing with me.
- I'm playing with him.

12:27.837 --> 12:29.797
No, I- I just...I just moved.

12:29.797 --> 12:31.157
Now we're talking.

12:31.157 --> 12:32.797
- You're playing with him?
- All right, so I'll watch.

12:32.797 --> 12:36.597
- Abe, Stu, Stanley.
- Hey, look who's here.

12:36.597 --> 12:38.557
- How are you?
- Terrible.

12:38.557 --> 12:41.037
- Worse. Worse.
- How's your nervous stomach?

12:41.037 --> 12:44.037
- You still got schpilkis?
- Why don't you have a seat?

12:44.477 --> 12:46.277
You need my heating pad?

12:46.277 --> 12:48.757
Back's a little sore.
Back's a little sore.

12:48.757 --> 12:51.397
All right, now I'm officially terrified.

12:51.397 --> 12:53.597
He doesn't have this many friends at school.

12:53.597 --> 12:56.557
So they do fly airplanes from Orange County to Miami.

12:56.557 --> 12:58.757
I wouldn't know.
I see so little of you.

12:58.757 --> 13:00.117
Ma!

13:02.117 --> 13:05.557
- You look better than ever.
- Yeah? I'm getting married.

13:05.957 --> 13:06.837
You remember Ryan.

13:06.837 --> 13:09.317
Of course. Who would forget, with those arms?

13:10.397 --> 13:13.437
You know, if I weren't engaged...ooh...

13:13.957 --> 13:15.957
Ah, there's my grandson.

13:16.197 --> 13:18.677
- Hello, bubeleh.
- Hello, Nana.

13:20.077 --> 13:24.557
I want you to tell me everything that's gone on for you this whole last year.

13:24.557 --> 13:28.677
Oh...I can barely remember what I had for dinner last night.

13:28.677 --> 13:30.877
- Please!
- Welcome to the club, yeah.

13:30.877 --> 13:32.237
- Me, too.
- You know.

13:33.517 --> 13:35.557
- You want to talk?
- Sure, I do.

13:35.957 --> 13:39.037
You keep an eye on him, make sure he doesn't die of old age, huh?

13:42.557 --> 13:45.877
Is this...some Mueslix Malted?

13:46.237 --> 13:47.997
Kirsten couldn't make it?

13:48.357 --> 13:50.317
Well...she wanted to.

13:52.277 --> 13:54.517
So how are things with you two?

13:55.037 --> 13:56.317
To be honest?

13:56.717 --> 13:58.157
They've been better.

14:00.557 --> 14:02.437
You two will work it out.

14:04.317 --> 14:06.317
Since when did you become such a romantic?

14:06.317 --> 14:08.397
Falling in love will do that to you.

14:08.397 --> 14:09.317
Speaking of which,

14:09.317 --> 14:15.277
I have photos from the place where we're holding the ceremony in June.

14:15.277 --> 14:17.357
So you should book your tickets now.

14:17.357 --> 14:19.277
Whoa, June? What's the rush?

14:19.277 --> 14:21.397
- Pregnant?
- Eh...very funny.

14:21.397 --> 14:25.397
Listen, you go through a year like I did, you don't want to waste any time.

14:25.397 --> 14:29.117
Besides...I want to move before the summer storms hit.

14:29.117 --> 14:30.637
- You're moving?
- Yeah.

14:30.637 --> 14:32.237
Bobby is 12 years my junior.

14:32.237 --> 14:34.357
This place skews a little old for him.

14:34.357 --> 14:37.157
We're going to move to the condo you bought me in Sarasota.

14:37.157 --> 14:38.797
Well, finally.
It was meant to be lived in.

14:38.797 --> 14:40.197
Bobby flipped when he saw it.

14:40.197 --> 14:42.717
Beach front, unbeatable location, why wouldn't he?

14:44.157 --> 14:45.997
I know what you're thinking, Sanford.

14:46.357 --> 14:48.917
And cynicism is a Cohen family trait.

14:48.917 --> 14:50.677
Yeah, well, I learned from the master.

14:50.677 --> 14:54.357
Yeah, well...nonetheless, he's a good guy.

14:54.357 --> 14:56.157
And he can move his practice anywhere.

14:56.157 --> 14:58.997
Everybody always needs a good chiropractor.

15:00.917 --> 15:02.477
Not another word.

15:04.837 --> 15:07.357
- I can't wait to meet him.
- Very good.

15:07.357 --> 15:09.797
- Eat your lunch.
- Yes, Ma.

15:16.997 --> 15:18.997
Hey, Summer?

15:21.717 --> 15:22.997
Oh, God.

15:22.997 --> 15:25.157
Zach, I'm so sorry.
Are you okay?

15:25.157 --> 15:26.277
I was in a rage blackout.

15:26.277 --> 15:28.517
My therapist told me that boxing might help me work through it.

15:28.517 --> 15:31.277
I came over to see if, uh, you were okay after the other night.

15:31.277 --> 15:34.917
I'm in gym clothes, and my hair is in French braids, so I'm terrible.

15:35.317 --> 15:38.037
Cohen and I are on a time- out.

15:38.877 --> 15:41.997
He went off to Miami, to, I'm sure, party it up like he always does

15:41.997 --> 15:43.717
this time of year when we're on a time- out.

15:43.717 --> 15:45.797
Well, are you too full of rage to hang out?

15:45.797 --> 15:47.037
Maybe come over for dinner?

15:47.037 --> 15:49.877
No offense, Zach, but hanging with your family couldn't sound worse.

15:49.877 --> 15:52.157
Oh, no. I totally understand.

15:52.157 --> 15:56.397
Um...they're in Aspen for an economics conference.

15:56.757 --> 15:59.157
Come on, I'll cook.
Italian.

15:59.917 --> 16:02.717
Francesca gave me a great recipe.

16:06.037 --> 16:08.197
Choke!
Sit down.

16:09.477 --> 16:11.717
Sorry, it's a figure of speech.
Victory lap.

16:16.837 --> 16:18.397
You cleaned his clock.

16:18.397 --> 16:21.197
Not that he'll pay up, that cheap bastard.

16:21.197 --> 16:22.677
All right, listen up.
What do you say?

16:22.677 --> 16:24.597
Uh, are you ready to roll?
'Cause I'm really hungry.

16:24.597 --> 16:26.677
Hey, I'm famished, too.

16:26.677 --> 16:29.077
It doesn't seem like there's anybody left to beat,

16:29.077 --> 16:30.837
so why don't we go into the dining hall?

16:30.837 --> 16:33.557
We're going to have lunch, my treat.

16:34.597 --> 16:37.157
- Can't beat that.
- Can I get in on the action?

16:39.117 --> 16:41.917
Mary Sue.
Nice to meet you.

16:42.197 --> 16:44.157
